e to do is <code>end - start<\/code> to obtain the length. <\/p>\n\n<p>A small scriptlet such as this would work in linux/cygwin terminal (I wont go in detail because this is not the scope of this forum):<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>awk -F \"\\t\" '$3==\"transcript\"{print $9, $5-$4}' file.gtf &gt; output.txt\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The <code>$9<\/code> refers to the ninth field which holds information about that feature including the gene name, gene id etc. <\/p>\n\n<p>The first link that I mentioned also shows some basic methods of extracting information from GTF.<\/p>\n","answer_id":17152,"question_id":17141,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1449652753},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2442ea911c89187262d6575d739a1ca7?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":5148,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5148/swbarnes2","reputation":1824,"display_name":"swbarnes2"},"score":2,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1399308404,"creation_date":1399308404,"body":"<p>I'd use Ensembl's BioMart.  It's not connecting for me right this second, but it should have that information.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ensembl.org/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ensembl.org/index.html<\/a><\/p>\n","answer_id":17167,"question_id":17141,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/17141/how-do-download-a-list-of-the-gene-length-of-all-genes","last_activity_date":1449652753,"creation_date":1399234481,"answer_count":2,"title":"How do download a list of the gene length of all genes?","body":"<p>I would like to get the gene length information of all the human genes. Is there a quick way to get this information? Thank you!<\/p>\n","question_id":17141,"tags":["bioinformatics"],"score":2,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":961,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1399282158},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/352620ba41c077bb6cf636b59bfd2fd3?s=128&d=identic