elling occurs, indicating that K+ doesn't enter in large amounts as a membrane potential is quickly created and quickly opposes any net inward flux of K+.<\/p>\n\n<p>However, when FCCP is added, a large amount of swelling occurs, indicating that something is entering the matrix and causing water to follow.<\/p>\n\n<p>Would this be CH3COOH? Ch3COOH can enter and dissociate into H+ and Ch3coo- , thus causing a pH gradient. H+ can be pumped out to remove this pH gradient.<\/p>\n\n<p>Does Valinomycin-K+ enter as well? If one H+ is pumped out for every H+ carried in by CH3COOH, would this make sense?<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/QHSQR.png\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/QHSQR.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n","question_id":41348,"tags":["cell-membrane","mitochondria","membrane-transport"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":19,"up_vote_count":0,"last_edit_date":1449607364},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/kpwGC.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6009,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6009/imprisoned-rhesus","reputation":250,"display_name":"Imprisoned Rhesus","accept_rate":75},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/INPrd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16651,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16651/amr","reputation":4081,"display_name":"AMR"},"score":7,"post_id":41268,"edited":false,"creation_date":1449379321,"comment_id":69909,"body":"It is black skin and fur. The blue is just a problem with the White Balance of the photograph. Remember the Blue Dress thing on Facebook earlier this year?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":0,"post_id":41268,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"h